France’s Juppe Says UN Condemnation of Syria Is ‘Important Step’

-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 
2011-08-04T09:41:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/france-s-juppe-says-un-condemnation-of-syria-is-important-step-.html
 The  United Nations Security
Council ’s condemnation of the escalating violence in Syria marks
“an important step,” France’s Foreign Affairs Minister  Alain
Juppe  said today.  “It’s the first time that the  Security Council  has
expressed itself unambiguously, condemned violence against the
civilian population and explicitly warned the Syrian
authorities,” he said in an interview on France Info radio.
“It’s an important step.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Steve Rhinds in Paris at 
